facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of women of reproductive age (aged 15-49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods (percent)

facts.fact_text: The adolescent birth rate declined from 17.2 births per 1,000 women aged 15-19 years in 2000 to 15.9 births per 1,000 women aged 15-19 years in 2017.
